<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1914-09-22T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1914-09-22T00:00:00-05:00" n="917" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d917">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 812.00/13258.</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of
                                    State</gloss> to Special Agent <persName type="to">Carothers</persName>.</hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-09-22">
                                    <hi rend="italic">September 22, 1914</hi></date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>Please say to General Villa that the President has received his telegram
                            of September 17 in which he expresses his appreciation of the
                            President’s action in ordering the American forces to withdraw from Vera
                            Cruz; that it has given the President much pleasure to receive General
                            Villa’s message; and that he hopes that the withdrawal <pb facs="0719" n="603" xml:id="pg_603"/> will be regarded by the Mexican people as
                            another evidence of this Government’s desire to lend its aid to bring
                            about the speedy establishment of a truly just and representative
                            government in Mexico.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Robert Lansing</hi></signed>.</closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>